
[1]keenness

   KEE'NNESS, n. Eagerness; vehemence; as the keenness of hunger.

   1. Sharpness; fineness of edge; as the keenness of a razor.

   2. The quality of piercing; rigor; sharpness; as the keenness of the
   air or of cold.

   3. Asperity; acrimony; bitterness; as the keenness of satire, invective
   or sarcasm.

   4. Acuteness; sharpness; as the keenness of wit.
